and determine what can be performed in house Ensure plant compliance with legal and regulatory requirements by informing the teams of the requirements and conducting regular reviews Participate in the maintenance budgeting process annually. Monitor actual expenses against budget monthly. Prepare daily, weekly and monthly maintenance reports using systemic and qualitative data. Oversee recruitment, recognition, performance management, remuneration, development and discipline of the section\u2019s maintenance team. Provide on the job coaching to the technicians and artisans in the team, develop their ability to perform predictive maintenance and problem solving The ideal candidate should have: Diploma Mechanical or Electrical Engineering (Heavy or Light Current) B.Tech or Bsc / BEng Degree in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering will be advantageous Government Certificate of Competence, Factories will be advantageous 7 years maintenance experience in heavy industry Some supervision experience will be advantageous CLOSING DATE: 15 July 2020 How to Apply? Please click on one of the buttons below. If you encounter any issue while applying contact your HR contact . Feel free to visit our website for further information www.sappi.com Sappi is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. Should you not have been contacted within 14 days of the closing date of this advert, please consider your application unsuccessful. Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
